akitaDAO.descr: the app ID of the Akita DAO

creatorRoyalty.descr: the amount the creator will get for the sale

endTimestamp.descr: The end time of the raffle as a unix timestamp

entryCount.descr: The number of entries for the raffle

entryID.descr: The id's of the raffle entries

findWinnerCursors.descr:
cursors to track iteration of finding winner
index being for the bid iteration
amountIndex being the index for the amount of the bids seen

gateID.descr: the gate to use for the raffle

isPrizeBox.descr: whether or not the prize is an asset or a prize box

marketplace.descr: the address of the creation side marketplace

marketplaceRoyalties.descr: the amount the marketplaces will get for the sale

maxTickets.descr: The maximum number of tickets users can enter the raffle with

minTickets.descr: The minimum number of tickets to use for the raffle

prize.descr: the prize for the raffle if prizeBox is true prize represents the app id of the prize box, otherwise the asset being raffled

prizeClaimed.descr: Indicator for whether the prize has been claimed

refundMBRCursor.descr: cursor to track iteration of MBR refunds

salt.descr: the transaction id of the create application call for salting our VRF call

startTimestamp.descr: The start round of the raffle as a unix timestamp

ticketAsset.descr: The asset required to enter the raffle

ticketCount.descr: The number of tickets entered into the raffle

version.descr: the current version of the contract

vrfFailureCount.descr: counter for how many times we've failed to get rng from the beacon

weightTotals.descr: totals for each box of weights for our skip list

weightsBoxCount.descr: the number of boxes allocated to tracking weights

winner.descr: the winning address of the raffle

returns.desc: a boolean of whether the auction is live

methods.name: optin

args.name: asset
args.desc: The asset to be opted into

methods.desc: optin tells the contract to opt into an asa
